narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: ENGL 114 01 is one of the easier English classes, with a lesser workload and very receptive professor. Though it was not the class I thought it would be (I expected a greater focus on literature), I did find that my reading of articles and scholarly journals did improve.

English 114 is touted as the "must take freshman writing class," but I think the section that you're in REALLY matters. My section gave me writing practice, but didn't really teach me any new writing skills. I don't think we mentioned the word thesis once in class the entire semester. Professor Walsh is really kind and tries to foster a community atmosphere in the class, and I enjoyed the readings, but I didn't feel like I learned very much.
I strongly recommend this course to any student who wishes to improve his or her writing skills. This course has helped me for writing assignments in other courses.

I would summarize ENGLE 114 01 for a fellow student as an excellent introductory writing course that gives you more insight into the function of the humanities in society. Yes, I would recommend this class to another student because I think that I was lucky to have taken such an interesting class with such engaging material.
